    "created_at": "2014-11-09T04:11:15Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-11-09T04:11:15Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "All working now.\n\nAfter some messy attempts at the full session reset, which would allow reconnect without refreshing the page, I don't seem to be able to do that cleanly. So this just enables 'kernel reconnect', which means it only enables reconnect if the kernel still exists. Refreshing the page is still required to re-establish connection if the session was deleted from another window, or the server has restarted.\n"
